history.content:
Hello and welcome to EECS 127/227!

Below are some announcements for the first week of the course:

  • Syllabus and Schedule
    • The syllabus can be found on bCourses (or here).  Please read it carefully.
    • A tentative schedule can be found here.
    • There will be no GSI office hours, or homework parties this week.
    • Discussion sections start this Friday (8/30)
    • We have put the schedule with lectures, office hours, discussions, etc. on a google calendar here (Links to an external site.)
    • We will keep this calendar updated with any changes to scheduling, so please be sure to refer to it when you have any questions about timing
  • Diagnostic Quiz
    • We will have an in-class diagnostic quiz on Tuesday (9/2).  This quiz does not count towards your final grade; its purpose is to help us get a sense of the spread of background knowledge in the class and for you to gauge your readiness for the class.
  • Homework
    • Homeworks will be submitted and self-graded on gradescope.  Please create a gradescope account using the following course entry code...
    • Homeworks will be assigned every Thursday and be due the following Thursday by 11:00pm
    • The first homework (Homework #1) will be released next Thursday (9/5). 
  • Practice problem
    • There will be optional (but recommended) practice problems on Gradescope, with entry code...
    • The practice problem will be posted weekly

From bcourse.
